title.narrative: OUTPUT 3.2: QUALITY AND INCLUSIVE EDUCATION

description.narrative: Education providers, parents and communities have improved knowledge and skills to contribute to quality learning in inclusive safe and protective school environments, which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Access To Quality Learning Opportunities (Covid), Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement (Covid), Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Innovation, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021, more children have access to early stimulation and quality basic education and learning in inclusive and safe school environments.

description.narrative: To improve quality learning in Sudan, 14,184 primary school teachers (61% women) have improved capacity in teacher pedagogy and learning environments.; UNICEF worked to strengthen the overall capacity of teachers, within the enabling environment with a Teacher Training Roadmap and the training of primary school teachers. And 167 schools were supported to become inclusive, safe and have protective school environment. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:18/01/2022
